@@TJvPreviewRenderControl.Stretch
Summary
  Indicates whether the Control preview should be changed so that it exactly fits the bounds of the
  container.
Description
  If Stretch is true, the image is changed to fill the entire available client area. If Stretch is
  false, the image is displayed at its original size.
See Also
  TJvPreviewRenderControl.Proportional

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderControl.Proportional
Summary
  Indicates whether the Control preview should be changed, without distortion, so that it fits the
  bounds of the container.
Description
  Use Proportional to set whether the Control preview is stretched to fill the entire client area or
  if it should be stretched to fill as much as possible without changing the original width to height
  ratio of the image. Proportional only have effect if Stretch is true.
See Also
  TJvPreviewGraphicItem.DestRect, TJvPreviewRenderControl.Stretch

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderControl.Control
Summary
  Indicates the control to render.
Description
  Use Control to specify the TControl descendant to render to the preview control. If Control is nil,
  no preview is generated when CreatePreview is called.
See Also
  TJvCustomPreviewRenderer.CreatePreview

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderControl.Center
Summary
  Indicates whether the preview is centered in its container.
Description
  Use Center to specify whether the TControl is rendered centered on the preview control

