Description
  The ToPage property corresponds to the To field in a Print dialog.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPrinter.FromPage

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.Title
Summary
  Determines the text that is listed in the Print Manager and on network header pages.
Description
  Title is used by Windows in the Print Manager and for network title pages.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.PrintRange
Summary
  Specifies whether FromPage and ToPage are valid.
Description
  Use PrintRange to determine whether FromPage and ToPage contains valid values. If PrintRange is
  prAllPages, FromPage and ToPage are ignored, otherwise they are considered valid.
  Note prSelection is not supported by the print preview components at his time.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.Printer
Summary
  Provides access to the global printer object.
Description
  \Read Printer to access the properties and methods of the TPrinter class.
See Also
  <DELPHILINK TPrinter>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.PrintPreview
Summary
  Specifies the print preview control that is responsible for creating the print job.
Description
  Set PrintPreview to a TJvCustomPreviewControl or descendant that should be handling the creation of
  the document to print. TJvPreviewPrinter does not itself provide methods for creating the document.
  Instead, it uses the <LINK TJvCustomPreviewControl.PrintRange, PrintRange> method of
  TJvCustomPreviewControl to do the actual work.
See Also
  TJvCustomPreviewControl

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.Print
Summary
  Starts the print job.
Description
  Call Print to send the document in the preview control to the printer. If a preview control is
  assigned to the PrintPreview property, its PrintRange method is called to do the actual printing.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPrinter.PrintPreview

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.Options
Summary
  Indicates the options to use when a print dialog is displayed.
Description
  Use Options to specify the print options to use when a print dialog is to be displayed. Options
  isn't
  used by TJvPreviewPrinter itself. It is only provided as a convenient way of storing the print
  dialog options without actually having to create a dialog to house them.
See Also
  <DELPHILINK TPrintDialog.Options>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.OnNewPage
Summary
  Occurs when a new page is to be printed.
Description
  Write a handler for OnNewPage to take specific action when a new page is about to be sent to the
  printer. For example, you can update the progress on a dialog shown to the user.
Parameters
  Sender    - The object that called the event.
  PageIndex - The number of the page that is to be printed.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPrinter.OnAbort, TJvPreviewPrinter.OnBeginDoc, TJvPreviewPrinter.OnEndDoc

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.OnEndDoc
Summary
  Occurs when the print job is finished.
Description
  Write a handler for OnEndDoc to take specific action when the print job has finished. For example,
  you could hide a dialog previously shown in OnBeginDoc.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPrinter.OnBeginDoc, TJvPreviewPrinter.OnNewPage

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.OnBeginDoc
Summary
  Occurs when the print job is started.
Description
  Write a handler for OnBeginDoc to take specific action when the print job starts. For example, you
  could display a dialog to the user while the printing is in progress.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPrinter.OnEndDoc, TJvPreviewPrinter.OnNewPage

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.FromPage
Summary
  Indicates the page on which the print job is to begin.
Description
  The FromPage property corresponds to the From field in a Print dialog.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPrinter.ToPage

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPrinter.OnAbort
Summary
  Occurs when the print job is aborted.
Description
  Write a handler for OnAbort to take specific action when the print job is aborted. For example, you
  could display a dialog to the user warning them that the print job was aborted or you could hide a
  progress dialog previously shown in OnBeginDoc.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPrinter.OnBeginDoc, TJvPreviewPrinter.OnEndDoc, TJvPreviewPrinter.OnNewPage

