@@TJvPreviewRenderStrings.Font
Summary
  Specifies the font settings to use in when rendering.
Description
  Use Font to specify the font settings to use when creating the preview. Changing the properties of
  the font won't be instantly visible in the preview. Call CreatePreview to update the preview.
See Also
  TJvCustomPreviewRenderer.CreatePreview

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewRenderStrings.Strings
Summary
  List of text strings that should be rendered.
Description
  use Strings to specify the text strings to render to the preview. You can copy strings from any
  other control or TStrings descendant by assigning directly to the Strings property or you can use
  the methods of TStrings (like Add, Remove, LoadFromFile etc) to define the content of the list.
  
  To view the new or changed content of Strings, you must call the CreatePreview method.
See Also
  TJvCustomPreviewRenderer.CreatePreview

